Huge fan of Chipotle, however, their customer service has gone down the toilet. When the pandemic started I would order pickup/delivery all the time. Unfortunately the order was wrong almost every time (missing item, missing side, extremely late). At first, chipotle and pepper were great at making things right however I seem to be on a blacklist or something because now when I report issues I'm just told "sorry, can't do anything, goodbye" I was literally hung up on. It's not my fault this restaurant can't get their orders correct. With the major price increases, chipotle is no longer affordable and not worth it since they don't value loyal customers. I went back today after a month or two off and my quesadilla was made wrong. After submitting the feedback, I was discarded again. I now run the risk of being stuck with an incorrect order EVERY TIME.  #disgusting #horriblecustimerservice #pepperisuseless #qdobatime

mentions.caption:
Chipotle is piloting a new responsible restaurant design that will help it progress toward its goal to reduce its direct and indirect greenhouse gas emissions 50% by 2030 (from 2019 baseline levels). You can visit restaurants with the new design in Gloucester, Virginia and Jacksonville, Florida. A third location will open in Castle Rock, Colorado this summer.
 
Key features of Chipotle’s responsible restaurants include:
- Rooftop solar panels, where feasible
- All-electric equipment and systems to replace gas power
- Smaller electric cookline
- Solar shading at the storefront
- Biodegradable serviceware such as cutlery, straws, bowls, cups, and lids
- Cactus leather chairs
- Artwork made from recycled rice husks 
- Electric vehicle charging stations at select locations
 
#chipotlepartner #chipotle #sustainability #restaurantdesign
